ament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":16,"text":"But they that escape of them shall be delivered, and shall be upon the mountains: and I will slay all , every one for his iniquities.","searchKeywords":["but","they","that","escape","them","shall","delivered","and","upon","the","mountains","will","slay","all","every","one","for","his","iniquities"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_17","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":17,"text":"All hands shall be completely weakened, and all thighs shall be defiled with moisture.","searchKeywords":["all","hands","shall","completely","weakened","and","thighs","defiled","with","moisture"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_18","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":18,"text":"And they shall gird themselves with sackcloth, and amazement shall cover them; and shame shall be upon them, upon every face, and baldness upon every head.","searchKeywords":["and","they","shall","gird","themselves","with","sackcloth","amazement","cover","them","shame","upon","every","face","baldness","head"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_19","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":19,"text":"Their silver shall be cast forth in the streets, and their gold shall be despised: their souls shall not be satisfied, and their bellies shall not be filled: for it was the punishment of their iniquities.","searchKeywords":["their","silver","shall","cast","forth","the","streets","and","gold","despised","souls","not","satisfied","bellies","filled","for","was","punishment","iniquities"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_20","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":20,"text":"their choice ornaments, they employed them for pride, and they made of them images of their abominations: therefore have I made them uncleanness to them.","searchKeywords":["their","choice","ornaments","they","employed","them","for","pride","and","made","images","abominations","therefore","have","uncleanness"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_21","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":21,"text":"And I will deliver them into the hands of strangers to make them a prey, and to the pests of the earth for a spoil; and they shall profane them.","searchKeywords":["and","will","deliver","them","into","the","hands","strangers","make","prey","pests","earth","for","spoil","they","shall","profane"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_22","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":22,"text":"And I will turn away my face from them, and they shall defile my charge, and shall go in to them unguardedly, and profane them.","searchKeywords":["and","will","turn","away","face","from","them","they","shall","defile","charge","unguardedly","profane"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_23","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":23,"text":"And they shall work uncleanness: because the land is full of strange nations, and the city is full of iniquity.","searchKeywords":["and","they","shall","work","uncleanness","because","the","land","full","strange","nations","city","iniquity"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_24","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":24,"text":"And I will turn back the boasting of their strength; and their holy things shall be defiled.","searchKeywords":["and","will","turn","back","the","boasting","their","strength","holy","things","shall","defiled"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_25","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":25,"text":"And propitiation shall come, and shall seek peace, yet there shall be none.","searchKeywords":["and","propitiation","shall","come","seek","peace","yet","there","none"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_26","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":26,"text":"There shall be woe upon woe, and there shall be message upon message; and a vision shall be sought from a prophet; but the law shall perish from the priest, and counsel from the elders.","searchKeywords":["there","shall","woe","upon","and","message","vision","sought","from","prophet","but","the","law","perish","priest","counsel","elders"]},{"verseId":"brenton_ezekiel_7_27","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":49,"bookName":"Ezekiel","bookAbbrev":"ezekiel","chapter":7,"verse":27,"text":"The prince shall clothe himself with desolation, and the hands of the people of the land shall be made feeble: I will do to them according to their ways, and according to their judgments will I punish them; and they shall know that I am the Lord.","searchKeywords":["the","prince","shall","clothe","himself","with","desolation","and","hands","people","land","made","feeble","will","them","according","their","ways","judgments","punish","they","know","that","lord"]}]